The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Feb. 4: The BSE and the NSE will carry out a special 90-minute trading session on Saturday to help NSE test an upgrade in its trading system. The special live trading session on February 6, in the cash and futures segments, will open at 11 am and close at 12:30 pm.                             
	 Mumbai, Feb. 4: An RBI-sponsored survey has forecast India would grow 7.9-8.8 per cent in 2010-11 depending on the global economy. The IMF said India would grow 6.75 per cent this fiscal and return to 8 per cent next year even if the developed world remained sluggish.                             
	 New Delhi, Feb. 4: The ministers of the coal and environment department will meet later this month to discuss the problems faced by Coal India in securing environmental clearances for its projects.                            
	 New Delhi, Feb. 4: India has received foreign direct investment worth $1.5 billion in December 2009, an increase of 10 per cent over $1.36 billion in December 2008.                             
	 Tokyo/ Washington, Feb. 4: US safety regulators have opened a formal probe into the problems with the brakes of Toyotas Prius. Toyota Motor expects costs and lost sales from its massive safety recall to total $2 billion by the end of March.                                                                                                                          
